{
  "stem": "24130.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was different for us-- the war was different than for my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a soldier and we were civilians, so it was entirely different for us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think we were very orthodox.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a shul, even 35 families, but there was no problem with having 10 people to daven every morning and every night.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a cheder-- where my brothers would go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had a mikveh-- a bath, ritual bath.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had-- I mean, a shochet that he would slaughter for meat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were very observant, very observant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ou shul didn't have a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think that all the people practically were rabbis, had [NON-ENGLISH], and they were capable to-- we just, the community had organized a president and-- and the shul was ran by the community.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was ordained as a rabbi, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "During the war?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think my father was-- to me, he was a father and a mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- when he came home, he would spend all the time with the children, talking to us, and explain us thing, and to teach us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he taught us how to cook, how to bake, how whatever I learned as a child, I learned from my father.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He would get up early in the morning and prepare for us things that we should have for the day, and he would come home at night to his [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if he came home, his-- that time belonged to the children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He would always go with us swimming.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he taught us how to swim, which he always felt is a very important thing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And because we lived near a lake, so I don't even remember how young I was when I start swimming.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
